      • registerCommands

        public java.util.Set<T> registerCommands(T... commands)
        Attempts to register a collection of ShortCommands

        The command manager will attempt to register each command individually. If it cannot be registered, the command is added to a set of other ShortCommands that could not be registered, which is then returned.

        Parameters:
        commands - The ShortCommands to add
        Returns:
        A set containing all commands that could not be added

      • exec

        public boolean exec(CommandWrapper command)
        Attempts to find and execute a ShortCommand based on the provided CommandWrapper

        If a command with a matching name is found, the command is executed and the method returns true. If the command is not found, the method returns false. This class is strictly for internal command handling, and should not be used under any circumstances

        Parameters:
        command - The CommandWrapper created from a server command
        Returns:
        Whether or not the command ran successfully
        See Also:
        CommandWrapper

      • disableCommand

        public boolean disableCommand(T command)
                       throws PersistentCommandException
        Disables a ShortCommand

        When a command is disabled, any calls to the command will be entirely ignored, and will be passed along to Bukkit's default command handling. The command itself is not unregistered, to prevent name conflicts should another plugin attempt to register a command with a matching name.

        Returns:
        Whether or not the command was successfully disabled
        Throws:
        PersistentCommandException
